    business tiers. We hoped to learn the first thought that lead customers to
    decide our product was a something useful to them.
  </p>
  <p>
    From the interviews, we have a more clear way of thinking about our customers
    and how we might continue to build a product they will love.
  </p>
  <p>
    We wanted to understand the context of our customers and the challenges they
    face in finding and using our product through the framework of
    <a href="http://www.elezea.com/2013/11/progress-making-forces/">forces</a>:
  </p>
  <ul class="bulleted-list">
